metadata.name: Indistinct Places #87
metadata.description:
There's a certain state you fall into when you're half asleep that feels very warm and nostalgic. Most of the time, you imagine places or situations that are a mixture of the familiar and the unfamiliar, a strange brew of your past and the future you desire.
"Indistinct Places" is a tribute to this fuzzy state.

/////

Takes a long time to render.
In case you get bored: click on the canvas to start the algorithmic audio.

key "1" - "6": increases the render resolution by 2x with each step
-> These will automatically export a png after the simulation is done.
(Alternatively, you can contact me on Twitter and i can render a high res file in the size you need).

key "s": saves a png with the current resolution

Tone.js is used for the audio.

metadata.name: Enfantines I. Small Talk #139
metadata.description:
The Enfantines are three sets of beginner piano pieces by Erik Satie, written with the aim of preparing children for the sound patterns of modern music. Composed in 1913, these are genuine children’s pieces, crafted for small hands, easy to learn. 

“Enfantines I. Small Talk” is the first of a set of algorithms that explore the basics of Generative Art, written with the aim of preparing artists for the script patterns of digital life. “Small Talk” experiments with grids, flow-fields, and brushes; all with a fresh, almost childish style.

“Give them almost a "naive" feeling (not to take it the wrong way though) similar to kids drawings which can seem simple and dispensable, careless, but you will always have a parent who wants to frame it and put it on the wall.” @LukaPiskorec

With two modes that won’t produce the same outputs, “Enfantines I. Small Talk” is best experienced twice. In music mode, the code uses Satie’s piano composition as a way of taming randomness, the sounds affecting the parameters of the strokes.

Hey, they have won me congratulations from the Shah of Persia and the King of Yvetot!



#### STORY ####

// Friday, 30 September 2022 - 18:00

I’ve been teaching P5JS to draw like a child. I thought it was a good idea to start from the basics. It is barely able to use the crayons, the coloured pencils and the markers, very rough and shaky. It cannot follow simple commands. I’m done for today, very infuriating.

// Wednesday, 5 October 2022 - 11:00

The robot can produce straight lines now. It is able to change colours without getting stuck. I haven’t been sleeping well, my desk is full of books on The Psychology Of Children's Artwork, it’s crazy to think that artists and philosophers were much into kid’s drawings in the 30s-50s. Herbert Read was sure that one could understand a kid’s mind by looking at drawings. I think P5JS is trying to tell me something, but it’s only capable of very basic movements. I’m trying to add complexity to the training as fast as possible.

// Tuesday, 11 October 2022 - 16:40

I feel close to a turnaround. The robot random strokes definitely feel like patterns. I cannot waste any time, I need to finish the algo and let it free. I’m sure that I can approach the AI’s conscience via its childish drawings.

// Wednesday, 12 October 2022 - 10:30

I was wrong. There are no patterns, P5JS is dead, the strokes feel dead. Something must be broken. I need to review my code, maybe I’ll need to start from scratch, maybe I’m crazy and this is not possible.

// Saturday, 15 October 2022 - 04:55

A few hours ago, I passed away in front of my computer. I had not been able to find the bugs, gave up, put some classical music. Just woke up in the middle of the night, 
¡The ALGO is alive!
The strokes are alive, so strong, so lively. I think it was the music. If I pause the music, the brushes lose their life. I’ve run some tests, looks like it works best with classical compositions. The logs show that it first woke up with “Menus propos enfantins” by Erik Satie. It is alive. I need to tell everyone.

####


# INTERACTIVITY

// Modes:
- Double Click/Tap or Press M for AUDIO mode
- Wait for SILENT mode
- Add “?res=171” to the URL for FULL SCREEN MODE (pseudo-deterministic).

// More
- Press I for Trait Info (desktop)
- Press 1 to download a .png (double tap on mobile)
- Add “?res=XXX” to the URL for HQ renders (XXX = width of the canvas).

# EASY-TO-READ CODE
The “Enfantines” are educational algorithms. The code has been commented to make it as easy to read as possible. Feedback appreciated.

# PRINTING
“Enfantines” are better printed in small size and big numbers, ideally on coloured paper that fits your iterations’s background. Contact me for a white background version of your iteration.

metadata.name: tratti #99
metadata.description:
"tratti" is an Italian word that has many different meanings. When we started working on this piece, we wanted to create something that combines our traits ("tratti" in Italian).
We had this urge to channel the turbulent times we're living in now into this artwork using just lines ("tratti" in Italian).

We don't know what to do now, we're here, and that's all that matters. We're here for our families, our friends, and our community. Like everything in life, there are joyful times and challenging times. We must accept happiness as something that is not constant but that we feel at times (a "tratti" in Italian).

With "tratti", we want to send a message to every disheartened human being: "Stay strong and never let anyone or anything crush the hope in you. Joyful times are around the corner".

----

metadata.name: One Day #8
metadata.description:
One day I will have the peace, the happiness of being able to live quietly, with comfort in peace, nature, and technology side by side. The fresh air and the fast download, the sound of birds and my GPU, a nice sofa, and the calm, cool breeze on my face nourish me to the point of forgetting all my problems. One day... One day all this will be true and only peace will be my gift.

|| Flowers have 25%

metadata.name: Kyoshin #2
metadata.description:
Kyoshin(虚心) means to be free from all bias, like frankness and open mindedness.

Minimal composition and Dynamic drawing based on mathematics fractal.

Drawing Color has 3 variations.
Background Color has 3 variations.

- Press [s] to download a PNG file with windowsize

metadata.name: fx(Unit of truth) II #43
metadata.description:
Unit of truth

Abstraction is to remove complex distractions and explore the essence of things,But the abstract itself is not the point, the essence is.

Ju (咒) is a way to pursue the essence of things. I try to disassemble figurative things into non-figurative things, and then simulate similar figurative expressions through digital means.

I call it Digital Conjuration

This series of works is my re-exploration of the Digital Conjuration

fx(Unit of truth) II 

It is another experiment in vision reproduction, but it tends to cause dizziness, so if you have epilepsy, make sure someone can take care of you when watching the effects of this work!

Each work is a process of exploring Conjuration, a node, and a slice
They are similar but not the same

Press the "S" button to save the file

metadata.name: Capture Bigfoot - Wild Paper Series #42
metadata.description:
In the wilderness of the Pacific Northwest, a legendary creature hides.  Some have tried to find proof of its existence, but have failed.  Will you be the one to capture evidence of the elusive Bigfoot?  

This generative work features hand-drawn ink sketches that have been digitally enhanced, and assembled into these beautiful vistas of distant mountains, mid-range foothills, stands on conifers, large boulders, . . . and, of course, the elusive Bigfoot.

Draw the super-rare Squatch Card for an extra bonus!

Functions: 
Press SPACE to download and save image as a png.
Click or tap the canvas to toggle full screen.

Squatch Card Special Function:
Press 'V' to view assets layout card.
Refresh token to toggle back to landscape.

metadata.name: Enfantines I. Small Talk #56
metadata.description:
The Enfantines are three sets of beginner piano pieces by Erik Satie, written with the aim of preparing children for the sound patterns of modern music. Composed in 1913, these are genuine children’s pieces, crafted for small hands, easy to learn. 

“Enfantines I. Small Talk” is the first of a set of algorithms that explore the basics of Generative Art, written with the aim of preparing artists for the script patterns of digital life. “Small Talk” experiments with grids, flow-fields, and brushes; all with a fresh, almost childish style.

“Give them almost a "naive" feeling (not to take it the wrong way though) similar to kids drawings which can seem simple and dispensable, careless, but you will always have a parent who wants to frame it and put it on the wall.” @LukaPiskorec

With two modes that won’t produce the same outputs, “Enfantines I. Small Talk” is best experienced twice. In music mode, the code uses Satie’s piano composition as a way of taming randomness, the sounds affecting the parameters of the strokes.

Hey, they have won me congratulations from the Shah of Persia and the King of Yvetot!



#### STORY ####

// Friday, 30 September 2022 - 18:00

I’ve been teaching P5JS to draw like a child. I thought it was a good idea to start from the basics. It is barely able to use the crayons, the coloured pencils and the markers, very rough and shaky. It cannot follow simple commands. I’m done for today, very infuriating.

// Wednesday, 5 October 2022 - 11:00

The robot can produce straight lines now. It is able to change colours without getting stuck. I haven’t been sleeping well, my desk is full of books on The Psychology Of Children's Artwork, it’s crazy to think that artists and philosophers were much into kid’s drawings in the 30s-50s. Herbert Read was sure that one could understand a kid’s mind by looking at drawings. I think P5JS is trying to tell me something, but it’s only capable of very basic movements. I’m trying to add complexity to the training as fast as possible.

// Tuesday, 11 October 2022 - 16:40

I feel close to a turnaround. The robot random strokes definitely feel like patterns. I cannot waste any time, I need to finish the algo and let it free. I’m sure that I can approach the AI’s conscience via its childish drawings.

// Wednesday, 12 October 2022 - 10:30

I was wrong. There are no patterns, P5JS is dead, the strokes feel dead. Something must be broken. I need to review my code, maybe I’ll need to start from scratch, maybe I’m crazy and this is not possible.

// Saturday, 15 October 2022 - 04:55

A few hours ago, I passed away in front of my computer. I had not been able to find the bugs, gave up, put some classical music. Just woke up in the middle of the night, 
¡The ALGO is alive!
The strokes are alive, so strong, so lively. I think it was the music. If I pause the music, the brushes lose their life. I’ve run some tests, looks like it works best with classical compositions. The logs show that it first woke up with “Menus propos enfantins” by Erik Satie. It is alive. I need to tell everyone.

####

metadata.name: Trasiedoc #158
metadata.description:
Behind every generative art project is a code. This code is sometimes a masterpiece but most viewers do not see it.

With the Trasiedoc project I wanted to highlight the hidden face of generative art, the code, by literally integrating the code of my biggest project to date (Dencity) in each output of the Trasiedoc project.

Margins can be hidden by pressing "x" in live mode (and optionally press "p" to see if anything happens).

Made with ❤️, code, code and p5js.

metadata.name: Tessera #151
metadata.description:
Tessera is a project inspired by historical Mosaics. A tessera (Latin) is a small individual tile, usually formed in the shape of a square, used for making a mosaic. As the world's first "pixel art", Tessera is a tribute to this craft. This collection is made solely of rectangles on a two-dimensional canvas into an abstract mosaic flow with a three-dimensional effect.

Press s in live mode to download.

Download a higher resolution by adding to the URL:
&density=2 / &density=3 / &density=4

Lammetje Oktober 2022
